# Frontend Architecture

The frontend is built using Next.js App Router with React Server Components and client components where needed.

## Component Structure

### UI Components
- [src/components/ui](mdc:src/components/ui) - Reusable UI components
- [src/components/video](mdc:src/components/video) - Video-specific components
- [src/components/comments](mdc:src/components/comments) - Comment system components

### Page Structure
- `/src/app/[locale]` - Main pages with i18n support
  - `/videos` - Video browsing and viewing
  - `/categories` - Category browsing
  - `/models` - Model browsing
  - `/admin` - Admin dashboard

### Utilities and Hooks
- [src/hooks](mdc:src/hooks) - Custom React hooks
- [src/utils/react](mdc:src/utils/react) - React-specific utilities
- [src/utils/server](mdc:src/utils/server) - Server utilities

## Internationalization
The app uses Next.js built-in i18n routing with [locale] segments. Translation files are stored in the [messages](mdc:messages) directory.
